Cut the rhubarb into 3cm/1in lengths and mix with the sugar and vanilla.Leave to macerate for a minimum of one hour or overnight if possible.Preheat oven to 170C/325F/ Gas 3.Lightly butter a baking dish, drain the rhubarb and pack it in. Cover tightly with foil and bake for twenty minutes.Remove from oven and leave until cool before uncovering.